BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:N_aVXb9_ZgIfFQQ-Jz5u3
SUMMARY:Founder Friday: Supercharging Human Potential in the Age of AI
DTSTAMP:20260205T082834Z
DTSTART:20260207T000000Z
DESCRIPTION:Join us for February’s Founder Friday with Sarah J. Ritter\, Ma
	naging Partner at Darkridge Digital and founder of AI startup Tribute. In 
	this session\, Sarah will explore what it means to lead at the intersectio
	n of artificial intelligence and human behavior\, drawing from her journey
	 across Microsoft\, early-stage ventures\, and her work in responsible inn
	ovation. \n\nStudents will gain insights into: \n\nHow AI can supercharge 
	human potential rather than replace it \n\nWhat founders and leaders shoul
	d consider when navigating uncertainty \n\nHow teams can build products an
	d cultures rooted in curiosity\, systems thinking\, and innovation \n\nIf 
	you’re interested in entrepreneurship\, product management\, or the future
	 of AI in everyday work\, this Founder Friday is for you. \n\nAbout Sarah\
	n\nI've always been fascinated by how people and systems work—which is why
	 I studied anthropology before building enterprise software for twenty yea
	rs. That combination has shaped how I lead: with deep curiosity about huma
	n behavior and a systems thinker's approach to solving complex problems. M
	y career has been defined by navigating transformation. At Microsoft\, I o
	rchestrated Windows 7\, 8\, and 10 launches during the shift from on-prem 
	to cloud. As founder of AI startup Tribute\, I learned what it takes to bu
	ild from zero—raising $3.5M and reaching $1M ARR. Now at Workato\, I'm hel
	ping reposition the company from iPaaS to Enterprise AI infrastructure. I'
	m an early AI adopter and serial tinkerer—I use Claude daily and experimen
	t openly with both wins and failures. I believe the best leaders’ model re
	sponsible innovation while keeping humans at the center of every technolog
	y transformation.\n\nAbout Founder Friday\n\nFounder Friday is a quarterly
	 event hosted by Seattle University’s Innovation and Entrepreneurship Cent
