BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:kosvQhWZ8fjaNWEkcfhA6
SUMMARY:Melodies of the Diaspora: Celebrating 100 Years of Black History Mo
	nth
DTSTAMP:20260205T082835Z
DTSTART:20260212T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:In celebration of Black History Month 2026\, the City of Bellev
	ue is working with community partners to present "Melodies of the Diaspora
	: Celebrating 100 Years of Black History Month\," an art exhibition featur
	ing the work of Pacific Northwest Black artists on display at the Bellevue
	 Arts Museum and Bellevue City Hall and is designed to take visitors on a 
	chronological journey of Black art through downtown Bellevue.\n\nThe exhib
	ition will feature paintings\, photography\, sculptures\, textiles and fas
	hion and is curated by Jay Taylor\, Fancy Vargas and Jerry Lee.\n\nFrom SE
	Atoday - All Events
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/melodies-of-the-diaspora-
	celebrating-100-years-of-black-history-month/18022797/2026-02-12T00
LOCATION:Bellevue Arts Museum\, 510 Belllevue Way NE\, Bellevue\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT7H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:nSRzMalXu50cXMkBdvB0w
SUMMARY:Bloodworks Northwest Blood Drive at Seattle Central College
DTSTAMP:20260205T082835Z
DTSTART:20260212T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:This Valentine’s Week\, be someone’s type. Give blood\, spread 
	love\, and help save lives.\n\nPatient needs are outpacing donations\, and
	 our local blood supply has reached emergency low levels. To keep up\, Blo
	odwork Northwest has had to bring in blood from other parts of the country
	\, a short-term fix as shortages are happening nationwide.\n\nLocal donors
	 are urgently needed to make sure patients in Pacific Northwest hospitals 
	have access to lifesaving transfusions for cancer treatments\, trauma care
	\, and birth complications.\n\nIf you’re feeling healthy\, show some love 
	and give blood. A small act from you can mean everything to someone else 💕
	\n\n🩸💘 Valentine’s Week Blood Drive Thursday\, Feb 12 Seattle Central Coll
	ege – Room BE-1110 10:00 AM – 4:00 PM\n\nBe someone’s type. Give blood.\n\
	nAppointments can be made at https://donate.bloodworksnw.org/donor/schedul
	es/sponsor\\_code or stop on by!\n\nFrom SEAtoday - All Events
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/bloodworks-northwest-bloo
	d-drive-at-seattle-central-college/17989011/2026-02-12T00
LOCATION:Seattle Central College\, 1701 Broadway- BE 1110\, Seattle\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT6H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:hVunW7PucgDNM01qlIZJp
SUMMARY:The Business Date - quality time with your other significant other.
DTSTAMP:20260205T082835Z
