BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:4XLDECMWkuCkNYcfVyONI
SUMMARY:Susan Meiselas: Crossings
DTSTAMP:20260205T082835Z
DTSTART:20260212T200000Z
DESCRIPTION:First presented at the Art Institute of Chicago in 1990\, this 
	exhibition by Susan Meiselas intertwines documentary photographs of Centra
	l America during the 1970s and 1980s \\(from Nicaragua and El Salvador\\) 
	along with panoramic images from the US/Mexico border taken in 1989. Addit
	ional photographs of the US/Mexico border taken in 2018 are also featured 
	in a site-specific gallery installation. The exhibition invites viewers to
	 see immigration in the context of economic and political crises in the re
	gion.\n\nToday\, the work feels newly urgent. US immigration enforcement h
	as expanded through militarization and constant surveillance\, with leader
	s using fear-driven language to divide communities and legitimize brutal f
	orms of control.\n\nThese photographs ask us to look carefully\, to recogn
	ize familiar patterns\, and to hold on to our shared humanity across the g
	lobe. People move in search of safety\, possibility\, and a better life fo
	r their families\, which is a universal hope that crosses borders\, genera
	tions\, and time.\n\nFrom SEAtoday - All Events
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/susan-meiselas-crossings/
	17977024/2026-02-12T00
LOCATION:Photographic Center Northwest (PCNW)\, 900 12th Ave.\, Seattle\, W
	A
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT9H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:w8YsjntpPBpAuySN8uMWF
SUMMARY:CEIE Leadership Academy Virtual Open House
DTSTAMP:20260205T082835Z
DTSTART:20260212T200000Z
DESCRIPTION:Center for Ecumenical and Interreligious Engagement\n\nOpen Hou
	se:\n\nCEIE invites you to join us for a virtual open house to learn more 
	about our Leadership Academy opportunities\, beginning with our winter hyb
	rid course on developing interreligious fluencies - Seeking Religious Lite
	racy!\n\n \n\nParticipants will get a preview of additional new self-paced
	 courses\, including our Summer 2026 Discerning Leadership Certificate pro
	gram. The Discerning Leadership program was launched last June and continu
	es this June \\(21-26\\)\, available to religious leaders and focused on a
	n immersive week of learning\, growing\, reflecting on leadership\, and pr
	eparing to engage in the public square each day.\n\n \n\nIn addition\, hea
	r from alumni about these educational programs and learn how to register. 
	 Executive Director and Spehar-Halligan Professor\, Michael Trice\, and As
	sistant Director\, Kara Markell\, lead us through the time together online
	! \n\n \n\nLearn more about the Center for Ecumenical and Interreligious E
	ngagement here \\>\\>  https://www.seattleu.edu/center-for-ecumenical-and-
	interreligious-engagement/ceie-leadership-academy/\n\nFrom SEAtoday - All 
	Events
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/ceie-leadership-academy-v
	irtual-open-house/17008239/2026-02-12T00
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H
END:VEVENT
