BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:p_Z4v3ZBYcWUDmowOOwKv
SUMMARY:Valentine's Day at Pike Place Market
DTSTAMP:20260205T082835Z
DTSTART:20260213T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Pike Place Market is the destination for showing love to Seattl
	eites and their beloveds\, family\, friends\, and even pets! The Market is
	 a one-stop shop for romantic dates\, one-of-a-kind gifts\, and beautiful 
	bouquets.\n\nOn Friday\, February 13\, from 10 am – 3 pm\, visitors can sh
	op bouquets from local farmers\, enjoy tasty donuts\, and pick up a Valent
	ine’s card designed by Market artists.\n\nEvent Highlights:\n\nFresh\, Loc
	ally Grown Flowers – Impress a loved one with an iconic bouquet from Pike 
	Place Market flower farmers. Additional flower vendors will be lining Pike
	 Place for the day\, offering an abundant selection for visitors to find t
	he perfect bouquet of tulips.\n\nLocally Designed Valentine’s Day Cards – 
	With every Market bouquet purchase\, visitors can stop by the tent under t
	he Clock & Sign from 10 am – 3 pm to pick up a free\, artist-designed Vale
	ntine’s Day card. This year’s cards were exclusively created by Market art
	ists.\n\nFarm-Fresh Donuts – Don’t miss a special\, one-day appearance by 
	9th and Hennepin Donuts serving up hot\, fried-to-order donuts. Their deca
	dent donuts\, handmade with locally sourced ingredients\, are a must-try. 
	Check their Instagram for the weekly flavor lineup.\n\nMake this Valentine
	’s Day one to remember with the charm and seasonal offerings of Pike Place
	 Market. Whether you’re planning a romantic dinner\, grabbing a last‑minut
	e bouquet\, sourcing high‑quality ingredients for a home‑cooked meal\, or 
	finding the perfect gift\, the Market is a must‑visit destination for both
	 Seattleites and visitors.\n\nFrom SEAtoday - All Events
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/valentine-s-day-at-pike-p
	lace-market/18018881/2026-02-13T00
LOCATION:Pike Place Market\, 85 Pike Street\, Seattle\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT5H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:MXbrs1dSl5mcXGZtbbvGL
SUMMARY:Melodies of the Diaspora: Celebrating 100 Years of Black History Mo
	nth
DTSTAMP:20260205T082835Z
DTSTART:20260213T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:In celebration of Black History Month 2026\, the City of Bellev
	ue is working with community partners to present "Melodies of the Diaspora
	: Celebrating 100 Years of Black History Month\," an art exhibition featur
	ing the work of Pacific Northwest Black artists on display at the Bellevue
	 Arts Museum and Bellevue City Hall and is designed to take visitors on a 
	chronological journey of Black art through downtown Bellevue.\n\nThe exhib
	ition will feature paintings\, photography\, sculptures\, textiles and fas
	hion and is curated by Jay Taylor\, Fancy Vargas and Jerry Lee.\n\nFrom SE
	Atoday - All Events
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/melodies-of-the-diaspora-
	celebrating-100-years-of-black-history-month/18022797/2026-02-13T00
LOCATION:Bellevue Arts Museum\, 510 Belllevue Way NE\, Bellevue\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT7H
END:VEVENT
